# RELEASE — zsh-snap-new

Version:  v2.3
Date:     2026-04-19
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed
Shell:    zsh 5.9+

---

## What's in this release

### v2.3 — Dry-run + TTY safety + UX improvements
- `--dry-run` flag — shows the snapper command without creating any snapshot
- `q=quit` option at every interactive prompt — clean exit without error
- Disk space info displayed before scenario table — colored (green/yellow/red)
- Sudo detection via `$EUID` — no subprocess needed
- All `read` prompts use `< /dev/tty` — safe when stdin is piped
- `snapper list-configs < /dev/null` — prevents TTY contention
- Input validation loop — retries on invalid scenario choice
- Custom reason sanitized: `|` → `-` to prevent CSV field corruption
- Config detection: `[[ -d /etc/snapper/configs/home ]]`

### v2.1 — Robust parsing + sudo detection + error handling
- Auto-detect sudo requirement — compatible with ALLOW_USERS/ALLOW_GROUPS
- CSV parsing in "Current state" and ID sections — locale-independent
- Config validation at startup with initialization instructions
- Post-creation exit code check + new_id != prev_id verification
- English-only confirmations `[y/N]`

### v1.0 — Initial release
- `snap-new` — fully interactive guided snapshot creation
- Step-by-step prompts: reason, config (root/home), type (standard/important), confirmation
- Auto-detects available snapper configs — `home` prompt only shown if config exists
- `--cleanup-algorithm timeline` always set
- `important=yes` userdata protects snapshot from automatic cleanup
- Colored ANSI feedback throughout
